      "content": "The dizziness and stiff neck could be related to the caffeine and dehydration, but it's also possible that the sudden headache triggered a temporary vertigo or neck spasm. Stress can indeed contribute to physical symptoms like these, but it's also possible that your body is just reacting to the physical shock of the headache. To alleviate these symptoms, try to sit comfortably, take slow, deep breaths, and rest for a bit – you might be surprised at how quickly they can resolve on their own.",
